OL,3,CWhat is the two-child benefit cap and
OL,4,Chow many kids does it impact?
OL,6,FOver 1.5 million children are
OL,7,Fcurrently living in households
OL,8,Faffected by the two-child limit, which
OL,9,Faffects one in nine children in the UK.
OL,11,FEstimates suggest that scrapping the
OL,12,Fcap could lift 350,000 children out of
OL,13,Fpoverty and reduce the depth of
OL,14,Fpoverty for a further 800,000 children.
OL,16,FAccording to the Institute for Fiscal
OL,17,FStudies (IFS), families with three
OL,18,Fchildren receiving benefits for the
OL,19,Ffirst two lose out on an average of
OL,20,F#3,455 a year.
