OL,3,CWhat is the two-child benefit cap and
OL,4,Chow many kids does it impact?
OL,6,FA child is said to be living in
OL,7,Fpoverty if they live in a household
OL,8,Fwith an income below 60% of the
OL,9,Fnational median income.
OL,11,FA household earning less than 50% of
OL,12,Fthe average income is defined as
OL,13,Fliving in "deep poverty."
OL,15,FThe Child Poverty Action Group also
OL,16,Fsays that 59% of families affected by
OL,17,Fthe cap have at least one parent in
OL,18,Fwork, arguing that the suggestion that
OL,19,Fthe cap encourages parents on benefits
OL,20,Fto work is unsupported by evidence.
